{{Sculpture-stub}}

This is a '''list of plain English words and phrases''' and the longer, more cumbersome words they can replace. The problem word is listed ''first''; the plain English alternative follows.

[[Plain English]] (or plain language) is communication in English that emphasizes clarity and brevity, and avoids technical language—particularly in official government or business communication. It uses simple, familiar words instead of lengthy, formal words,{{sfn|Schiess|2003-2004|pp=71–75}} avoids [[jargon]], prefers positive words to negative words,{{sfn|SEC|1998|p=27}} and prefers strong verbs to [[Be (verb)#English|''be'' verbs]].{{sfn|Garner|2001}}
{{compact ToC|side=yes|top=yes|num=yes}}

==A==

*'''[[wikt:above-mentioned|above-mentioned]]''', '''above-listed''', '''before-mentioned''', '''aforementioned''' – (omit)<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2002|pp=100–01}}: "cumbersome phrases; lawyerisms"</ref><ref name="auto">{{harvnb|Wydick|1978|p=739}}: "lawyerism"</ref>
*'''[[wikt:abundance|abundance]]''' – enough, plenty, (or specific amount){{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''[[wikt:accede#Usage notes|accede to]]''' – allow, agree to{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''[[wikt:accelerate|accelerate]]''' – speed up{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''[[wikt:accentuate|accentuate]]''' – stress{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''[[wikt:accommodation|accommodation]]''' – room<ref name="auto1">{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=371}}: "formal word"</ref>
*'''[[wiktionary: accompany|accompany]]''' – go with,{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}} with{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''[[wiktionary: accomplish|accomplish]]''' – do{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: accorded|accorded]]''' – given{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: accordingly|accordingly]]''' – thus, so{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}<ref name="auto2">{{harvnb|Schiess|p=1}}: "heavy connector"</ref>
*'''[[wiktionary: accrue|accrue]]''' – add, gain{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: accurate|accurate]]''' – right{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: acquiesce|acquiesce]]''' – agree{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''[[wiktionary: acquire|acquire]]''' – get{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''[[wiktionary: additional|additional]]''' – extra{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}<ref name="auto3">{{harvnb|Plain English Campaign|2001|p=10}}: "word to avoid"</ref><ref name="auto2"/>
*'''[[wiktionary: address|address]]''' – discuss{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: addressees|addressees]]''' – you{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''adjacent to''' – Next to{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: adjustment|adjustment]]''' – change, alteration{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''[[wiktionary: admissible|admissible]]''' – allowed, accepted{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''[[wiktionary: advantageous|advantageous]]''' – helpful{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''adversely impact on''' – hurt, set back{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: advise|advise]]''' – tell{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}<ref name="auto3"/>
*'''afford an opportunity''' – allow, let{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''aggregate''' – total{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''[[wiktionary: aircraft|aircraft]]''' – airplane (USA) / aeroplane (UK){{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}} (''"Plane" can also mean "flat surface" and a woodworking tool; the word "airplane" avoids this confusion. The word "aircraft" can be used if you need to specifically include balloons, blimps, gliders, etc.; it's the simplest word for the whole category of aerial vehicles.'')
*'''[[wiktionary: alleviate|alleviate]]''' – ease, reduce{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''[[wiktionary: allocate|allocate]]''' – divide{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''along the lines of''' – like, as in{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|2001|p=4}}
*'''[[wiktionary: alternatively|alternatively]]''' – or{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|2001|p=4}}
*'''[[wiktionary: ameliorate|ameliorate]]''' – improve, help{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|2001|p=4}}
*'''an absence of''' – no, none{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|1998|p=3}}
*'''and particularly''' – particularly<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=611}}: "unnecessary"</ref>
*'''and/or''' – use either "and" or "or."{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}{{sfn|Garner|2002|p=102}}
*'''[[wiktionary: anticipate|anticipate]]''' – expect{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''a number of''' – some{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: applicant|applicant]]''' – you<ref name="auto3"/>
*'''[[wiktionary: application|application]]''' – use{{sfn|Plain English Campaign|2001|p=4}}
*'''[[wiktionary: apparent|apparent]]''' – clear, plain{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: apprehend|apprehend]]''' – arrest<ref name="auto4">{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=587}}: "officialese"</ref>
*'''[[wiktionary: appreciable|appreciable]]''' – many{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: appropriate|appropriate]]''' – proper, right{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: approximate|approximate]]''' – about{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}<ref name="auto5">{{harvnb|Garner|2009b|p=91}}: "genteelism"</ref>
*'''arrive onboard''' – arrive{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
