[[File:20140806Nudelbild.jpg|thumb|right|A picture made by using pasta]]
'''Macaroni art''', sometimes referred to as '''macaroni crafts''' or '''pasta art''', is artwork that is made of dry [[macaroni]] or [[List of pasta|other pasta]].<ref name="parents">{{cite web|url=http://www.parents.com/fun/arts-crafts/kid/pasta-crafts/|title=Use Your Noodle: 6 Crafts to Make with Pasta|publisher=parents.com|accessdate=2014-09-18}}</ref> The works commonly consist of individual pieces of macaroni glued to a surface to produce a [[mosaic]]. However, works may take the form of sculptures.

This type of art is produced during arts and crafts classes at pre-school.<ref name="artistshelpingchildren">{{cite web|url=http://www.artistshelpingchildren.org/pastacraftsideasactivitieskids.html|title=Pasta Crafts for Kids: Ideas for Arts and Crafts Activities with Spaghetti & Macaroni Noodles for Toddlers, Children, and Preschoolers|publisher=artistshelpingchildren.org|accessdate=2014-09-18}}</ref> Today, it has evolved to become an artform practiced by adults.{{Citation needed|reason=Questionable|date=November 2017}}

==In popular culture==
Pasta art was used to advertise a [[Nancy Sinatra]] concert at the world famous [[Fillmore West|Fillmore Auditorium]] in San Francisco. The art the poster was made from is composed entirely of ''Pasta e Fagioli'' (pasta and beans). Alphabet pasta spells out the lyrics for her hit "These Boots Are Made For Walking".<ref name="nancy sinatra">{{cite web|url=http://www.classicposters.com/Nancy_Sinatra/poster/New_Fillmore_Series/194|title=Nancy Sinatra at the Fillmore Auditorium, San Francisco, CA June 28, 1995|publisher=Classicposters.com|accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref>  

Another example of pasta art was featured in an episode of the television sitcom ''[[Seinfeld]]''. [[Cosmo Kramer]] produced a small sculpture made of [[fusilli]] called "Fusili Jerry".

